caption: I would have to say I am disappointed in the tardiness of this Dunkin opening in the morning. Today the staff didn't arrive and open until 620am, 20 minutes late. I have been two other times with a five and ten minute delayed opening. The staff should be there before 6am (the scheduled opening time) preparing to open the doors on time. Very unprofessional and wasting everyone's valuable time. The coffee and food is good as usual.

I was in this location (90 Broad St New York, NY  10004 United States) of Dunkin Donuts on august 12th at 1240 PM and was concerned as even though the sign on the front door says mask required to enter and all other locations require a mask the two workers (Girl and a guy) did not have masks on and were touching and rubbing there face while handling orders - we are in the middle of a pandemic and global health crisis and when I ask the girl working with no mask why she isn’t wearing one even though it says it’s required on the front door she laughed and said she doesn’t care and doesn’t need to - I then asked the guy why neither of them were and he followed her lead and had the same answer. I took a photo and will be sending it to corporate as I let the workers know because I think it’s completely unsanitary, unprofessional and if they can’t even easily put on a mask I can only imagine how lazy they are when it comes to actually cleaning the place. Will not be back and will be letting everyone know in the neighborhood as I have lived here for five years and it’s a shame my local Dunkin’ Donuts is not able to follow NY guidelines for covid-19

caption: This is my favorite of the two in the area. They have always been very helpful and listen to my order while the one around the corner is a bit iffy. No place to hang out here. This one is a get it and go type of place. Remember reviewers, depending on the time, service could vary. I never am there in the morning doing rush hour so can't attest to service during then. Usually afternoons or evenings and weekends is when I visit. Also, all Dunkin do it's like many fast food restaurants and service varies. Fast turn over at these types of places because owners probably make a quick buckand sell out,so finding some sort of consistency in staff and quality could vary when it comes to feedback.
